+# CLAUDE.md
+
+This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.
+
+## What this service does
+
+`cer-suite-cl-local-synchro-srv` is a Java 25 / Spring Boot 4 service with a single responsibility: consume a Pub/Sub
+event describing a file sitting in GCS, look up the destination POS controller for a store, download the file, and
+push it to that controller's TCx Sky API. It is intentionally generic/domain-agnostic — it used to be coupled to
+"devoluciones" (returns) but was decoupled so any producer can use it (see `INTEGRACION_SYNCHRO_CONTROLLER.md`).
+
+Flow:
+
+```
+Producer service
+  -> uploads file to GCS
+  -> publishes TransferEvent to Pub/Sub topic retail.local.synchro.controller.v1
+
+cer-suite-cl-local-synchro-srv
+  -> SynchroControllerSubscriber consumes retail.local.synchro.controller.v1-sub (routed by subscriptionId,
+     see PubSubRoutingProperties)
+  -> TransferMessageHandler deserializes TransferEvent, validates required fields, sets MDC (eventId/codStore/
+     correlationId), maps to TransferCommand
+  -> TransferFileUseCase.transfer(TransferCommand) -> TransferFileService
+       1. StoreQueryPort.findByCode(codStore)   -> queries MN_TIENDA (SAADMIN DB) for controller IP
+       2. GcsFileDownloadPort.download(bucket, path) -> downloads file bytes from GCS
+       3. FileTransferPort.transfer(storeConfig, targetDir, fileName, content)
+  -> TcxSkyFileTransferAdapter POSTs to https://{controllerIp}:8033/api/v1/files
+       body: { file, dir, content (base64) }, Authorization: Bearer <token from Secret Manager, cached>
+```
+
+Ack/Nack semantics matter here: `TransferMessageHandler.handle` returns `true` (ack, drop message) for invalid
+payloads, `StoreNotFoundException`, and `FileTransferPermanentException`/`IllegalArgumentException` (4xx-class,
+non-retryable errors). It returns `false` (nack, retry) for `FileTransferTransientException` and any unexpected
+exception (5xx/timeout-class, transient errors). When adding new failure modes, classify them into the permanent vs.
+transient exception hierarchy correctly — miscategorizing silently drops messages or causes infinite redelivery.
+
+## Architecture (hexagonal)
+
+Source under `src/main/java/com/elrosado/synchrosrv`:
+
+- `domain/model` — records: `TransferCommand`, `TransferResult`, `StoreTransferConfig`.
+- `domain/exception` — `StoreNotFoundException`, `FileTransferPermanentException`, `FileTransferTransientException`.
+- `domain/port/in` — `TransferFileUseCase` (the one inbound use case).
+- `domain/port/out` — `StoreQueryPort`, `GcsFileDownloadPort`, `FileTransferPort`, `BearerTokenPort`.
+- `application/service` — `TransferFileService`, the sole orchestrator implementing the use case; it only calls
+  ports, never infrastructure directly.
+- `infrastructure/adapter/in/event` — Pub/Sub inbound: `SynchroControllerSubscriber` (subscribes, routes by
+  subscriptionId, dispatches onto a virtual-thread executor), `TransferMessageHandler` (JSON parsing, validation,
+  MDC, exception-to-ack/nack mapping), `TransferEvent` (wire record).
+- `infrastructure/adapter/out/db` — `StoreQueryAdapter` (implements `StoreQueryPort`) + `MnTiendaEntity` +
+  `JpaMnTiendaRepository`, all scoped to the SAADMIN datasource.
+- `infrastructure/adapter/out/storage` — `GcsFileDownloadAdapter`, wraps `jlib-storage`'s
+  `IGoogleCloudStorageService`.
+- `infrastructure/adapter/out/transfer` — `TcxSkyFileTransferAdapter`, builds the TCx Sky request and maps HTTP
+  client/server errors to the permanent/transient exception pair.
+- `infrastructure/adapter/out/security` — `SecretManagerBearerTokenProvider`, fetches and caches (TTL-based,
+  double-checked locking) the TCx Sky bearer token from Secret Manager.
+- `infrastructure/config` — `PubSubRoutingProperties` (`app.pubsub.*`), `TransferProperties` (`app.transfer.*`,
+  also builds the TCx Sky URL), `MultiSqlSharedConfig`/`SaadminDataSourceConfig` (wires the `jlib-multisql` SAADMIN
+  datasource + JPA repositories), `HttpClientConfig` (trust-all SSL `RestClient` for TCx Sky — controllers use
+  self-signed certs on an internal network, this is intentional), `ThreadConfig` (virtual-thread executor).
+- `infrastructure/exception/GlobalExceptionHandler` — `@RestControllerAdvice` for the (minimal) web surface;
+  the actual business/domain never goes through it, since the entry point is Pub/Sub, not HTTP.
+
+Tests in `src/test/java` mirror this package structure 1:1.
+
+### Naming convention
+
+Keep names generic/domain-agnostic (`TransferFileService`, `TransferEvent`, `SynchroControllerSubscriber`, etc.) —
+do not reintroduce domain-specific naming like "devoluciones"/"returns". Input ports go in `domain.port.in`, output
+ports in `domain.port.out`, orchestration in `application.service`, adapters in `infrastructure.adapter`.
+
+## Event contract
+
+Producers publish to Pub/Sub topic `retail.local.synchro.controller.v1`; this service consumes from
+`retail.local.synchro.controller.v1-sub`. Required fields: `codStore`, `gcsBucket`, `gcsPath`, `fileName`,
+`targetDir`. Recommended: `eventId`, `eventType`, `source`, `createdAt`. Full contract, rules, and a sample payload
+are in `INTEGRACION_SYNCHRO_CONTROLLER.md` — read it before changing `TransferEvent`/`TransferCommand` or the
+validation in `TransferMessageHandler.isEventValid`.
+
+Key rules: `targetDir` and the GCS location are event data (per-message), never static service configuration —
+there is intentionally no `app.transfer.pos-target-dir` property. `gcsPath` should be relative (no leading `/`);
+the adapter strips leading slashes defensively but producers should avoid sending them.
+
+## Build, test, and run
+
+- `.\mvnw.cmd clean package` (Windows) / `./mvnw clean package` (Unix) — build + run tests. Use the Maven wrapper,
+  not a system Maven install.
+- `.\mvnw.cmd test` — run unit tests and generate the JaCoCo report (`jacoco-maven-plugin` runs on the `test` phase).
+- `.\mvnw.cmd test -Dtest=TransferFileServiceTest` — run a single test class.
+- `.\mvnw.cmd spring-boot:run "-Dspring-boot.run.profiles=local"` — run locally against the `local` profile
+  (`application-local.yaml`), which points at a real SAADMIN SQL Server instance and local GCP credentials
+  (`credentials_cer.json`, path is machine-specific — expect to need your own).
+- `bash build.sh` — builds a Podman image via `docker/dev/Dockerfile` and pushes it to the local dev registry
+  `localhost:30500`; also participates in Skaffold's dynamic tagging via the `$IMAGE` env var.
+- Deployment manifests live in `k8s/` (Deployment, HPA, ConfigMap, Secret, Service, Namespace); `skaffold.yaml`
+  ties the build and k8s deploy together for local dev loops.
+
+There is no separate lint command; rely on the compiler/tests.
+
+## Configuration
+
+Two Spring profiles: `local` (`application-local.yaml`) and `prod` (`application-prod.yaml`), selected via
+`SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE` (defaults to `local`). Notable property groups:
+
+- `app.pubsub.subscription-synchro-controller` — must match the Pub/Sub `subscription-id` under `pubsub.subscriptions`
+  for `SynchroControllerSubscriber` to route messages correctly; both are driven by the same
+  `PUBSUB_SUBSCRIPTION_SYNCHRO_CONTROLLER` env var in `prod`.
+- `app.transfer.*` — `enabled` (kill switch, event is acked-and-dropped when false), `api-port`/`files-path`
+  (used to build the TCx Sky URL), `timeout-seconds`, `bearer-token-secret-id`/`-version`/`-cache-ttl-seconds`
+  (Secret Manager token caching).
+- `multi-sql.datasources.saadmin.*` — SQL Server connection to SAADMIN, `entity-packages` scoped to
+  `infrastructure.adapter.out.db.entity.saadmin`.
+
+Dependencies come from private internal `jlib-*` shared libraries (logging, health, pubsub-logging, storage,
+multisql, secretmanager) resolved from the `SUITE-CLOUD` Azure DevOps Maven feed in `pom.xml` — these provide the
+Pub/Sub subscriber (`IMessageSubscriber`), GCS client (`IGoogleCloudStorageService`), and multi-datasource wiring
+used throughout `infrastructure/`.
+
+## Commit conventions
+
+Use concise imperative messages with optional prefixes like `feature:`, `fix:`, or `test:` (Spanish descriptions
+are common in this repo's history). PRs should describe the behavior changed, list configuration/deployment
+impacts, include test evidence, and link related work items when available.

